The Chronicle Business Reporter
ZIMBABWE Miners Federation (ZMF) president, Ms Henrietta Rushwaya, has been re-elected as the federation’s president for the next five years. This follows the recent ZMF national elections in which three other national executive members also retained their positions, the federation’s spokesperson, Mr Dosman Mangisi said in an interview. “Ms Rushwaya together with three other national executive members have retained their positions. “Mr Marufu Sithole is the vice-president, Mr Morgan Mugawu is the secretary-general and Mr Lufeyi Shato as treasury general have won the elections unopposed,” he said.